<h2 id="sunday_school">Sunday School Programs</h2>

<p>
    All children and youth begin in worship service and then are dismissed for classes, which include teacher led,
    Bible-based, age-appropriate lessons, discussions, crafts, songs, and prayer. We currently have five classes from
    infant through high school. College and Career aged adults remain in the worship service on Sundays with occasional
    fellowship events scheduled on her dates.
</p>
<p>
    <span class="bold">Nursery for infants - ages 0-2</span>
    Children up to age 2 meet together for a time of childcare and play under the guidance of experienced adult.
</p>

<br><br>

<div class="section">
    <div><img src="res/LIONSANDLAMBS.gif"></div>
    <img class="floatleft" src="res/PreSchool-01.gif">

    <p>
        <span class="bold">"LIONS AND LAMBS" Pre-K thru K Class</span>
        Meets in room #1. An experienced staff person provides individualized attention and care for the children.
        Children
        have Bible stories read to them, playtime, and craft activities available. The classroom contains it's own
        restroom.
    </p>
</div>

<br><br>

<div class="section">
    <div><img src="res/CHRISTTHELIGHT.gif"></div>
    <img class="floatleft" src="res/Elementary-01.gif">

    <p>
        <span class="bold">"CHRIST THE LIGHT" Children (1st thru 4th grade)</span>
        Meets in room #2. The typical program includes Bible stories, crafts, snacks, free time, and singing. If this is
        your first time at New Life, please feel free to sit in with your child until she or he is comfortable with the
        class.
    </p>
</div>

<br><br>


<div class="section">
    <img class="floatleft" src="res/1d20bf393fb358d7ffff9d347f000101.jpg">

    <p>
        <span class="bold">"JeLo" (Jesus Loves!) Middle Youth - (5th - 8th grades)</span>
        Meets in room #3. Teachers utilize Bible-based, age appropriate, lessons in a fun, relaxed, and supportive
        environment. The curriculum engages students with a variety of activities which could include discussion,
        computers,
        games, or crafts."
    </p>
</div>

<br><br>


<div class="section">
    <img class="floatleft" src="res/Middle-Youth-02.gif">

    <p>
        <span class="bold">"Covenant" Youth Programs - (9th - 12th grades)</span>
        Meets in various settings or off campus at First Presby. Castro Valley. This class includes mature High
        Schoolers.
        Lessons range from in-depth Bible studies to lively discussions of current events seeking to understand how God
        is
        present in their lives today. On months with five Sundays, this class participates in "Youth Sunday" as
        greeters,
        ushers, prayer leaders, praise team singers, and scripture readers.
    </p>
</div>

